A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 8 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 employment and training of police officers, so as to require the Georgia Peace Officer
3 Standards and Training Council to create and maintain an at-risk adult training course
4 focusing on officer response to individuals with Alzheimer's disease or dementia; to provide
5 for requirements for such course; to provide for collaborative course development with the
6 Division of Aging Services; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
7 other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Chapter 8 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to employment and
11 training of police officers, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
12 "35-8-28.
13 (a) The council shall create and maintain an at-risk adult training course available to all
14 peace officers relating to responding to at-risk adults, including those individuals living
15 with Alzheimer's disease or other form dementia.
16 (b) Such training course shall, at a minimum, provide training in:
