17 (1) Investigating criminal violations involving benefits trafficking and related offenses;
18 (2) Investigating criminal violations involving the abuse, neglect, or exploitation of a
19 disabled adult or elder person;
20 (3) Responding to reports of missing persons;
21 (4) Interacting with victims of abuse, neglect, and exploitation in a victim centered and
22 trauma informed way; and
23 (5) Certain aspects of Alzheimer's disease and other forms of dementia and cognitive
24 impairment, including;
25 (A) Instruction in interacting with persons with Alzheimer's disease and other forms
26 of dementia;
27 (B) Techniques for recognizing the behavioral symptoms and characteristics of
28 Alzheimer's disease and other forms of dementia;
29 (C) Techniques for effective communication with persons with Alzheimer's disease and
30 other forms of dementia;
31 (D) Techniques for employing alternatives to physical restraints; and
32 (E) Protocols for contacting caregivers when an individual with Alzheimer's disease
33 or other form of dementia is found wandering or during an emergency situation.
34 (c) The training course provided for in this Code section shall be developed by the council
35 in collaboration with forensic special initiatives unit of the Division of Aging of the
36 Department of Human Services.
37 (d) The number of hours and specific curriculum required for the training course provided
38 for in this Code section shall be at the discretion of council."
39 SECTION 2.
40 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
